<p>I had the same problem.  The chocolate must be cool in order to stick to the coconut oil, or it just slides right off.  The cooler the chocolate, the better.  I also had a problem squishing my coconut oil down after freezing - it cracked on the side, so I had to roll it into a ball to soften it (I really made an oily mess of my kitchen).  After a couple of tries, these were really great.  I wonder if I could add some shredded coconut for texture.</p>
