<li class="comment even depth-2" id="li-comment-37198">
<div id="comment-37198">
<div class="comment-author">
jo</div>
<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://www.elanaspantry.com/peppermint-patties/#comment-37198">March 18, 2011 at 1:58 pm</a></div>
<p>I couldn't get the chocolate to stick either, so I let the coconut mixture (I used raw honey instead of agave) sit after I froze them and I cooled my chocolate chips down to nearly room temperature.  This resulted in them turning into a mass of chocolate.  I took hunks of the mass and put it on the cold coconut mixture and rolled it with my warm hands.  I added more if it didn't cover the whole coconut ball  and they ended up looking more like chocolates you get in a box then patties.  Regardless they were very tasty and we each ate two.  I might add some shredded coconut next time to mine, just for something different. </p>
<p>One thing is for sure, you can't put hot chocolate even on the frozen coconut mixture, it melts it.</p>
