<div class="comment-author">
Ali</div>
<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://www.elanaspantry.com/peppermint-patties/#comment-12743">March 16, 2010 at 1:35 pm</a></div>
<p>I used raw honey and kept the amount the same, possibly used slightly less. I hope this helps you. My choice to use honey is based purely on cost and that it is a local product I can buy in my town which helps the local businesses and is more "green" than ordering from online. Sometimes I use maple syrup depending on the recipe--not for these, maple and mint just don't mix for me.  :-)</p>
<p>I've also found that if the sweetener is a main source of liquid then I should keep the amount. If not, I often use less to cut down on the sweetness.</p>
